Package: globalopt
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian Global Optimization Methods from the 'GlobalMinimum' Library
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Jonas", "Mockus", role = "aut",
           comment = "author of the original MINIMUM/GlobalMinimum Fortran library (1989)"),
    person("Audris", "Mockus", email = "audris@utk.edu", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Bindings to the 'GlobalMinimum' Fortran library of Bayesian and
    other global optimization methods by Jonas Mockus (1989), including the
    one-step Bayesian method ('BAYES1'), Monte-Carlo baselines ('MIG1',
    'MIG2'), Bayesian search with local refinement ('LBAYES'), clustering
    ('GLOPT'), uniform deterministic search ('UNT'), one-dimensional and
    coordinate-wise Wiener-model search ('EXTR', 'EXKOR'), LP-tau
    deterministic search ('LPMIN'), a variable-metric local method
    ('MIVAR4'), a flexible-tolerance constrained simplex ('FLEXI'),
    recursive quadratic programming ('REQP'), and variable-screening
    procedures ('ANAL1', 'ANAL2').  The original Fortran code is compiled
    into the package; objectives can be supplied as R functions or chosen
    from the built-in compiled test objectives.  A pure-R reference
    implementation of the core methods is included for comparison.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/audrism/globalopt
BugReports: https://github.com/audrism/globalopt/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
NeedsCompilation: yes
Depends: R (>= 3.5)
Imports: stats
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0.0), knitr, rmarkdown, GenSA, DEoptim, GA, nloptr,
    microbenchmark, optimx, minqa
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
